course: 50 and 100 mile options. Refer to www.cachegranfondo.com for maps and course information.

title: Huntsman World Senior Games
description:
40K - Division I: M 50-64; W 50-54 
40K - Division II: M 50-64

course: Begins at I-15 Exit 2 Southern Parkway towards the airport. Out and back course consisting of rolling hills, majestic views of Pine Valley Mountain and desert vistas.
registration: Early bird registration for athletes begins March 1, 2017 and ends August 1, 2017.  The fee is $79 + a $20 sports fee per event.  After August 1st, the registration fee goes up to $99.  Registration closes September 1, 2017. Register at www.seniorgames.net

title: Huntsman World Senior Games
description: Three start locations: 62K-Ivins; 50K-Gunlock Turnoff; 37K-Gunlock. Circuit course - 1 lap = 62K; start/end 3,000 feet altitude; rollies, 1,700 foot gain/loss, upgrades mostly under 6% but one 9% (0.4 mile), one 6%-11% (1.1 mile).
course: Long downhill, fast, twisty, challenging descent through scenic Snow Canyon State Park (reverse Hill Climb) near finish.
